### King James Version: Psalms Chapter 13

<span id="001">1</span> How long wilt thou forget me, O LORD? for ever?
how long wilt thou hide thy face from me?  

<span id="002">2</span> How long shall I take counsel in my soul, having
sorrow in my heart daily? how long shall mine enemy be exalted over
me?  

<span id="003">3</span> Consider and hear me, O LORD my God: lighten
mine eyes, lest I sleep the sleep of death;  

<span id="004">4</span> Lest mine enemy say, I have prevailed against
him; and those that trouble me rejoice when I am moved.  

<span id="005">5</span> But I have trusted in thy
[mercy](../ebd/ebd249.htm#005.md); my heart shall rejoice in thy
[salvation](../ebd/ebd320.htm#003.md).  

<span id="006">6</span> I will sing unto the LORD, because he hath dealt
bountifully with me.  

